    "body": "Thanks @jreback for the quick response. My previous example is over simplified, what about the following example\n\n``` python\ndf = pd.DataFrame([\n        ['A', 1, 85],\n        ['A', 2, 45],\n        ['A', 3, 23],\n        ['B', 4, 76],\n        ['B', 5, 43],\n        ['B', 6, 56]\n    ], columns=['Key', 'Value', 'Age'])\n\ndf1 = df.groupby('Key') \\\n    .agg({\n            'Value': {'V1': 'sum', 'V2': 'count'},\n            'Age': {'AvgAge': 'mean', 'StdAge': 'std'}\n        })\n```\n\nIs there a way to handle multiple columns aggregation with multiple aggregation method in a convenient way?\n"
